WEBVTT

00:01.569 --> 00:02.968
        [ Remote clicks ]

00:02.969 --> 00:04.570
     [ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.041 --> 00:10.009
 � I don't care what you say! �

00:11.278 --> 00:13.278
   � I'm gonna do what I want
           all day! �

00:13.280 --> 00:15.881
  � I'm the king of the world!
  I'm the king of the world! �

00:15.883 --> 00:17.816
   � I'm the king of the world!
   I'm the king of the world! �

00:17.818 --> 00:22.287
  � I'm the king of the world!
  I'm the king of the world! �

00:25.526 --> 00:27.960
     [ Italian music plays ]

00:29.697 --> 00:31.530
           Principal:
     This has been, by far,

00:31.532 --> 00:33.799
      one of the best years
    for Aberdale Elementary.

00:33.801 --> 00:35.334
    I'm so proud of you all.

00:35.336 --> 00:36.902
 Now, I know you're all excited

00:36.904 --> 00:41.373
       for Papa Marianio's
    big pizza summer kickoff.

00:41.375 --> 00:43.008
         [ Kids cheer ]

00:43.010 --> 00:46.178
  But first, the Spirit Awards
         from Mr. Reese.

00:46.180 --> 00:48.047
         [ Kids groan ]
                 Yes!

00:48.049 --> 00:51.316
           Thank you.
    Thank you, Mr. Principal.

00:51.318 --> 00:52.584
                 Jeff: Whoo!

00:52.586 --> 00:54.353
       Okay, Jeff cool it.

00:54.355 --> 00:55.988
    Now let's get this thing
           over with.

00:55.990 --> 00:58.323
 I got a list of awards, so I'm
   just gonna go through them.

00:58.325 --> 00:59.525
                     Uggggh!

00:59.527 --> 01:00.826
          Sumo, shush!

01:00.828 --> 01:04.029
   The award for Most Punctual
           goes to...

01:04.031 --> 01:05.397
             Darlie.

01:05.399 --> 01:07.332
             What?!

01:07.334 --> 01:08.934
Hey, Sumo.
                    What?

01:08.936 --> 01:11.603
Remember the last assembly,
 when it seemed like

01:11.605 --> 01:14.740
Papa Marianio wasn't gonna
show up to give us pizza,

01:14.742 --> 01:16.075
like he always does?

01:16.077 --> 01:17.209
                    Yeah?

01:17.211 --> 01:19.711
But then he parachuted down
  from the rafters

01:19.713 --> 01:21.113
     dressed up
  like a pepperoni?

01:21.115 --> 01:22.281
                    Yeah!

01:22.283 --> 01:24.716
But that wasn't even as cool
  as two years ago,

01:24.718 --> 01:27.419
when he had a cannon
that shot out cheesy sticks!

01:27.421 --> 01:29.521
 [ Imitates cannon ]

01:29.523 --> 01:30.856
             [ Laughing ] Yeah!

01:30.858 --> 01:34.393
Yep, he's pretty much
a real-life superhero.

01:34.395 --> 01:35.761
          [ Both sigh ]

01:35.763 --> 01:37.696
        You guys talking about
            Papa Marianio?

01:37.698 --> 01:40.232
        I heard that
  for every pizza he sells,

01:40.234 --> 01:41.533
        he gives one
         to charity.

01:41.535 --> 01:42.801
          Guys, please.

01:42.803 --> 01:45.604
        It's just pizza.
   You eat it, and it's gone.

01:45.606 --> 01:47.139
       Awards are forever.

01:47.141 --> 01:49.108
         They determine
      how we're remembered.

01:49.110 --> 01:51.610
     Eh, everyone just remembers
     what they want to remember.

01:51.612 --> 01:54.613
   I remember when Papa Marianio
   designed the original version

01:54.615 --> 01:56.882
           of the Aberdale flag,
             and it was a pizza!

01:56.884 --> 01:58.317
                  Yeah!
         Yeah!
     Yeah!

01:58.319 --> 01:59.785
        It's just pizza!

01:59.787 --> 02:01.820
     Come on, guys. I worked
    really hard to win these.

02:01.822 --> 02:05.457
     Okay, now for the award
   for Best Active Reading --

02:05.459 --> 02:07.459
   whatever that means, eh...

02:07.461 --> 02:08.627
             Breehn.

02:08.628 --> 02:10.762
          Who's casting
         these ballots?

02:10.764 --> 02:13.065
      [ Sighs ]
   Papa Marianio.

02:13.067 --> 02:14.133
      My hero.

02:14.135 --> 02:17.669
   This one time,
when I was just a wee boy...

02:17.671 --> 02:19.304
  <i> I wanted to see</i>
<i> if I took the hat off</i>

02:19.306 --> 02:21.473
<i> the Rough Rider's statue</i>
  <i> if it would turn</i>

02:21.475 --> 02:24.409
  <i> from a metal man</i>
<i> back into a regular meat man.</i>

02:24.411 --> 02:27.146
  <i> But when I tried</i>
 <i> to pull it off...</i>

02:27.148 --> 02:29.148
           Whoa! Ohh!

02:29.150 --> 02:32.751
<i> ...Papa Marianio saved me</i>
<i> with his pizza dough!</i>

02:32.753 --> 02:35.621
 He's my pizza hero.

02:35.623 --> 02:38.957
         Okay, now, uh,
       Best Teacher is...

02:38.959 --> 02:41.994
           It's a tie!
      Uh, me and Ms. Baker!

02:41.996 --> 02:42.828
              Hmm?

02:42.830 --> 02:44.196
     Where are ya, Melanie?

02:44.198 --> 02:46.532
          Come up here
  so we can accept it together.

02:46.534 --> 02:48.000
                 Ugh! Yeesh!

02:49.670 --> 02:52.838
   Hey, guys! Can't wait till
  Papa Marianio gets here, huh?

02:52.840 --> 02:55.174
He's my hero!    Yeah! Pizza!
     Not you, too, Ms. Baker.

02:55.176 --> 02:56.508
      I know. He's amazing!

02:56.510 --> 02:58.610
         This one time,
         I was so sad...

02:58.612 --> 03:01.280
      [ Crying, sniffling ]

03:02.516 --> 03:04.049
           [ Grunts ]

03:04.051 --> 03:07.352
  ...uh, because...my cat died.
     [ Chuckles nervously ]

03:07.354 --> 03:10.289
 [ Crying, sniffling continue ]

03:10.291 --> 03:11.490
        [ Knock on door ]
              Huh?

03:11.492 --> 03:14.059
       <i> And Papa Marianio</i>
       <i> brought me a pizza</i>

03:14.061 --> 03:15.494
              Hey!
      <i> in the shape of a --</i>

03:15.496 --> 03:16.628
           a -- a cat.

03:16.630 --> 03:18.630
           [ Laughs ]

03:18.632 --> 03:20.532
     I-I said "cat," right?

03:20.534 --> 03:24.036
  You guys know his restaurant
    has a "C" rating, right?

03:24.038 --> 03:25.837
           Mr. Reese:
      Let's see...um, uh...

03:25.839 --> 03:28.407
    Most Studious goes to...

03:28.409 --> 03:30.242
          Oh, oh! Shh!

03:30.244 --> 03:31.376
        I-It's my moment.

03:31.378 --> 03:32.411
        Mr. Reese: Percy!

03:32.413 --> 03:34.746
          [ Grunting, groaning ]

03:37.484 --> 03:38.684
                    Ooh!

03:38.686 --> 03:41.086
                 Thank you,
          Abderdably Elementary.

03:41.088 --> 03:43.388
      I will really, really like
                 this award.

03:43.390 --> 03:46.425
 Percy, you don't --
you don't have to give a speech.

03:46.427 --> 03:48.227
               Quiet, you man!

03:48.229 --> 03:49.428
       Ehh...

03:49.430 --> 03:53.665
      Um, also, there is someone
              I want to thank.

03:53.667 --> 03:55.601
             So, this one time,
               my bike broke,

03:55.603 --> 04:00.305
   and he -- Papa Marianionio --
             he -- he came up...

04:01.242 --> 04:02.541
            Oh! Ooh!

04:02.543 --> 04:04.176
            [ Wails ]

04:04.178 --> 04:05.978
        Hey!
                    Huh?

04:08.415 --> 04:09.615
        Hey!

04:09.617 --> 04:11.583
               Yay-ay-ay-ay...

04:11.585 --> 04:15.420
               ...ay-ay-ay-ay-
               ay-ay-ay-ay --

04:15.422 --> 04:16.755
     How was that helpful?!

04:16.757 --> 04:18.557
                    Hey!
              He saved my life!

04:18.559 --> 04:21.093
                 It started
             like any other day.

04:21.095 --> 04:23.328
            1,003...

04:25.399 --> 04:27.933
            1,004...

04:29.970 --> 04:30.769
              Huh?

04:30.771 --> 04:31.770
          [ Rumbling ]
              Whoa!

04:31.772 --> 04:33.538
    This thing's gonna blow!

04:33.540 --> 04:34.873
   Heeeeeeeeeeey!

04:34.875 --> 04:37.309
     <i> And out of nowhere...</i>

04:37.311 --> 04:38.610
            [ Boom! ]
     Unnnnnh!

04:38.612 --> 04:41.446
        <i> ...he took the hit</i>
      <i> that was meant for</i> me.

04:43.317 --> 04:45.284
           What was he
       even doing there?!

04:45.286 --> 04:48.153
      One time, he ran out
     of those normal boxes,

04:48.155 --> 04:51.390
     so he gave me my pizza
in a bunch a weird little boxes.

04:51.392 --> 04:53.659
   Hey, I ran out
  of regular boxes,

04:53.661 --> 04:55.327
   so I'm a-gonna
 give you the pizza

04:55.329 --> 04:57.729
     in a bunch
  of <i> little</i> boxes.

04:57.731 --> 04:58.764
    Here you go!

04:58.766 --> 04:59.998
Oh! Here's some more!

05:00.000 --> 05:02.834
  Hold on a-tight!
I got some more for ya!

05:02.836 --> 05:04.636
   <i> Made a whole doggie house</i>
          <i> out of them.</i>

05:04.638 --> 05:07.139
          [ Barking ]
        <i> Tiger loved it!</i>

05:07.141 --> 05:09.508
      Papa M -- great guy.
               Mm.

05:09.510 --> 05:11.510
 He taught me about pie charts!

05:13.013 --> 05:18.750
Well, he made me a custom pizza
  with none of my allergens.

05:18.752 --> 05:20.752
               He taught Chad
          about pie charts, too!

05:24.825 --> 05:28.694
       [ Pizzas moaning ]

05:28.696 --> 05:29.828
              Hey!

05:29.830 --> 05:32.931
     [ Laughing maniacally ]

05:32.933 --> 05:34.833
          [ Laughter ]

05:34.835 --> 05:36.201
      Chelsea:
Stop! My sides hurt!

05:36.203 --> 05:38.670
           Oh, you're
  one of the good ones, Gilben.

05:38.672 --> 05:39.871
              Okay.

05:39.873 --> 05:42.607
      Best smile goes to...

05:42.609 --> 05:43.608
              Jeff!

05:43.610 --> 05:45.077
    [ Gasps ] It's happening!

05:47.348 --> 05:51.950
  Well, Aberdale, it is an honor
             to win this award!

05:51.952 --> 05:53.385
       And I just want to say --

05:53.387 --> 05:55.320
            Papa Marianio...
Papa Marianio...
           Papa Marianio...

05:55.322 --> 05:57.322
    One time, he delivered pizza
                to our house

05:57.324 --> 06:00.325
         and he brought an extra
  kibble pizza for all our dogs.

06:00.327 --> 06:03.061
 Chad and me had our first date
       in Marianio's One.

06:03.063 --> 06:05.831
  [ Indistinct conversations ]

06:05.833 --> 06:07.833
     You people are deluded!

06:07.835 --> 06:09.701
        Huh?!   Huh?!
Huh?!           Huh?!

06:09.703 --> 06:12.704
   Clarence, he wasn't trying
  to break your fall that day.

06:12.706 --> 06:15.640
   He was just stealing dirty
 rainwater for his pizza dough.

06:15.642 --> 06:18.877
  Percy, replacing a bike wheel
        with a pizza pie

06:18.879 --> 06:21.813
       i-i-i-is the logic
          of a maniac!

06:22.516 --> 06:25.150
           [ Squeaking ] Oh, no!

06:25.152 --> 06:28.720
   Chelsea, that was your dad
who taught you about pie charts.

06:28.722 --> 06:30.856
              Chad,
   that was also Chelsea's dad

06:30.858 --> 06:33.024
         who taught you
        about pie charts.

06:33.026 --> 06:35.260
           Ms. Baker,
   isn't it kind of unsettling

06:35.262 --> 06:37.429
          that he knew
  about your romantic troubles?

06:37.431 --> 06:40.766
                 Ms. Baker:
      What?! Romantic troubles?!
    No, it was my cat, remember?

06:40.768 --> 06:43.301
           [ Sobbing ]

06:45.272 --> 06:46.238
            And Sumo!

06:46.240 --> 06:48.673
   [ Sobbing ]
           Heeeeeeeeeeey!

06:48.675 --> 06:50.175
     Daaaaaaaah!

06:50.177 --> 06:52.244
             Oh, yeah, that <i> was</i>
           at Ms. Baker's house.

06:52.246 --> 06:53.578
    What?! Why?!

06:53.580 --> 06:55.881
       Jeff, you don't even know
      what you're talking about.

06:55.883 --> 06:58.049
                Papa Marianio
               saved my life.

06:58.051 --> 06:59.518
       Oh, did he, Belson?

06:59.520 --> 07:01.052
                  Yes.
             Did he?

07:01.054 --> 07:03.054
                Yes, he did!
            Did he?!

07:03.056 --> 07:05.857
    Remember when I fell off
the roof and broke all my bones?

07:05.859 --> 07:07.592
     All right,
he needs more fluids.

07:07.594 --> 07:09.127
 If his O sats drop any farther,
   we're gonna have to intubate!

07:09.129 --> 07:10.762
    How's his heart working?

07:10.764 --> 07:12.697
                [ Wheezing ]

07:12.699 --> 07:14.900
      Mama mia!
     A-My boy-a!

07:14.902 --> 07:16.768
Try some of-a Papa's sauce!

07:16.770 --> 07:19.438
     Ehh! Gaah!
  Aa-- Aa-- Uhhh...

07:19.440 --> 07:20.572
                  [ Gulps ]

07:20.574 --> 07:23.875
                 [ Weakly ]
         Thank you, Santa Claus.

07:23.877 --> 07:26.745
     What good did that do?!

07:26.747 --> 07:29.781
   Papa Marianio isn't a hero!

07:29.783 --> 07:32.184
         He's a weirdo!

07:33.220 --> 07:37.656
         Well, I-I guess
      he has a point there.

07:37.658 --> 07:40.892
           I feel like something
         inside of me just died.

07:40.894 --> 07:44.563
  It can't be true.
I-I won't believe it.

07:44.565 --> 07:46.331
             Man! I'm so bummed!

07:46.333 --> 07:48.900
          I don't want
        to go on living.

07:48.902 --> 07:50.335
         That's better.

07:50.337 --> 07:52.737
      Now, as I was saying,
   I may have won Best Smile,

07:52.739 --> 07:57.642
 <i> but</i> it's only because you all
 give me so much to smile about.

07:57.644 --> 08:01.446
  So go on and give yourselves
      a round of applause.

08:01.448 --> 08:02.781
          [ Chuckles ]

08:02.783 --> 08:04.216
              Huh?

08:05.686 --> 08:08.820
   Come on. Are you guys still
  thinking about that Marianio?

08:08.822 --> 08:11.857
What'd Papa Marianio
ever do to you? Huh?

08:11.859 --> 08:13.658
    Nothing. Nothing at all.

08:13.660 --> 08:14.860
        He's just weird.

08:14.862 --> 08:16.528
      Come on!
  What did he do?!

08:16.530 --> 08:19.297
    Fine! You want to know?!
         I'll tell you!

08:19.299 --> 08:22.167
          I'll tell you
     all the grisly details!

08:22.169 --> 08:23.802
    <i> It was my 7th birthday,</i>

08:23.804 --> 08:26.271
      <i> and I had made sure</i>
  <i> that everything was perfect.</i>

08:26.273 --> 08:27.105
            Perfect!

08:27.107 --> 08:29.774
    <i> Until it was pizza time.</i>

08:29.776 --> 08:30.709
           [ Splat! ]

08:31.612 --> 08:32.477
          [ Whimpers ]

08:32.479 --> 08:34.779
                 Jeff,
        did you say something?

08:34.780 --> 08:38.015
          [ Screaming ]

08:38.018 --> 08:39.351
       [ Thunder crashes ]

08:39.352 --> 08:42.554
That doesn't sound like
  his fault at all.

08:42.556 --> 08:45.524
    Well, everyone remembers
   what they want to remember.

08:45.526 --> 08:47.826
             Why would you want
              to remember <i> that?</i>

08:47.828 --> 08:49.227
 I want to remember

08:49.229 --> 08:51.696
  that he gives out
free cheesy sticks -- for free!

08:51.698 --> 08:54.733
I want to remember that he saved
  my cat from a fire one time.

08:54.735 --> 08:58.203
         I want Chad to remember
    how to tie a tie without me.

08:59.373 --> 09:00.539
        Let's face it --

09:00.541 --> 09:03.141
      For a creepy weirdo,
       he was a great guy.

09:03.143 --> 09:05.744
     [ Indistinct talking ]

09:05.746 --> 09:07.078
         [ Horn honks ]

09:07.080 --> 09:09.214
                  It's him!

09:09.216 --> 09:11.883
        [ Kids cheering ]

09:11.885 --> 09:14.152
    Pizza? Whoo!

09:14.154 --> 09:15.687
     [ Laughs ]
 Pizza, here I come!

09:15.689 --> 09:18.290
                But...I won.

09:21.828 --> 09:23.728
          Hooray, Jeff!

09:23.730 --> 09:25.163
       A-Jeff is a winner!

09:25.165 --> 09:29.067
    [ Chuckles ]
Oh. Thank you, Papa Marianio.

09:29.069 --> 09:31.736
   You really are
   the best of us.

09:31.738 --> 09:33.738
                    Look!
              He's over there!

09:33.740 --> 09:35.707
        [ Kids cheering ]

09:35.709 --> 09:39.044
      All right, Aberdale,
   let's hear it for the Papa!

09:39.046 --> 09:41.346
        [ Kids cheering ]

09:43.216 --> 09:45.717
       [ Cheering stops ]

09:45.719 --> 09:48.687
    [ Papa Marianio laughs ]

09:48.689 --> 09:50.589
     [ Panting ]

09:50.591 --> 09:51.856
   Sorry I'm late!

09:51.858 --> 09:52.924
     Did I win?

09:52.926 --> 09:55.927
          [ Laughing ]

09:55.929 --> 09:57.762
         W-Why is he --

09:57.764 --> 09:59.598
     Wha-- What's happening?

09:59.600 --> 10:02.634
 Why did you tell us
 all that bad stuff
 about our memories?

10:02.636 --> 10:04.803
      Why'd you pour pizza sauce
               down my throat?

10:04.805 --> 10:08.139
   And how come you knew about
   Jeff's 7th birthday party?

10:08.141 --> 10:10.442
          Ah! Well-a...

10:10.444 --> 10:14.112
         Well, I guess-a
   I stubbed my toes recently.

10:14.114 --> 10:16.915
     Uh, I missed a delivery
          to my house,

10:16.917 --> 10:20.418
   and I had to go to the post
    office earlier this week.

10:20.420 --> 10:24.456
             But...
   if you were to ask-a me...

10:24.458 --> 10:27.892
 I guess-a the real answer is...

10:27.894 --> 10:29.260
             pizza!

10:29.262 --> 10:32.330
           [ Laughs ]
        [ Kids cheering ]

10:36.269 --> 10:39.070
            You guys!
         He remembered!

10:39.072 --> 10:40.639
     [ Cheering continues ]

10:40.641 --> 10:42.073
              Wow.

10:42.075 --> 10:45.477
          [ Laughing ]

10:45.479 --> 10:47.278
            Whaaaaa!

10:47.280 --> 10:48.647
          [ All gasp ]

10:50.017 --> 10:52.417
        [ Slow clapping ]

10:59.292 --> 11:02.193
          [ Applause ]

11:05.699 --> 11:07.532
        � Early to bed �

11:09.102 --> 11:11.236
        � Early to rise �

11:12.539 --> 11:14.673
       � Picking my nose �
